  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "kind": "summary",
        "title": "Summary",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Inner product of two arrays."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Ordinary inner product of vectors for 1-D arrays (without complex\nconjugation), in higher dimensions a sum product over the last axes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "parameters",
        "title": "Parameters",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "a, b",
            "type": "array_like",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "If `a` and `b` are nonscalar, their last dimensions must match."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "returns",
        "title": "Returns",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "out",
            "type": "ndarray",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "If `a` and `b` are both\nscalars or both 1-D arrays then a scalar is returned; otherwise\nan array is returned.\n``out.shape = (*a.shape[:-1], *b.shape[:-1])``"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "notes",
        "title": "Notes",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "For vectors (1-D arrays) it computes the ordinary inner-product::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "    np.inner(a, b) = sum(a[:]*b[:])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "More generally, if ``ndim(a) = r > 0`` and ``ndim(b) = s > 0``::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "    np.inner(a, b) = np.tensordot(a, b, axes=(-1,-1))"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "or explicitly::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "    np.inner(a, b)[i0,...,ir-2,j0,...,js-2]\n         = sum(a[i0,...,ir-2,:]*b[j0,...,js-2,:])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "In addition `a` or `b` may be scalars, in which case::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "   np.inner(a,b) = a*b"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "examples",
        "title": "Examples",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Ordinary inner product for vectors:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> import numpy as np\n>>> a = np.array([1,2,3])\n>>> b = np.array([0,1,0])\n>>> np.inner(a, b)\n2"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Some multidimensional examples:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> a = np.arange(24).reshape((2,3,4))\n>>> b = np.arange(4)\n>>> c = np.inner(a, b)\n>>> c.shape\n(2, 3)\n>>> c\narray([[ 14,  38,  62],\n       [ 86, 110, 134]])"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> a = np.arange(2).reshape((1,1,2))\n>>> b = np.arange(6).reshape((3,2))\n>>> c = np.inner(a, b)\n>>> c.shape\n(1, 1, 3)\n>>> c\narray([[[1, 3, 5]]])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "An example where `b` is a scalar:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.inner(np.eye(2), 7)\narray([[7., 0.],\n       [0., 7.]])"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "see-also",
        "title": "See Also",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "tensordot \u2014 Sum products over arbitrary axes."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "dot \u2014 Generalised matrix product, using second last dimension of `b`."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "vecdot \u2014 Vector dot product of two arrays."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "einsum \u2014 Einstein summation convention."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}